Binary: `0100 0000 0000 0000`
7-bit chunks: `000 0000` (0), `001 0000` (16), `000 0000` (0) -> wait.
16384 / 128 = 128 rem 0. Chunk 0: 0
128 / 128 = 1 rem 0. Chunk 1: 0
1 / 128 = 0 rem 1. Chunk 2: 1
Chunks (LSB first): `[0, 0, 1]`
Reversed: `[1, 0, 0]`
Set continuation: `[1|0x80, 0|0x80, 0]` -> `[0x81, 0x80, 0x00]`. Matches example `81 80 00`.

